    <h1>How to Write a Privacy Policy for an App</h1>
    <p class="last-updated">Published July 17, 2026</p>

    <p>To write a privacy policy for an app, identify every type of personal data your app collects, explain why you collect it and who receives it, describe how users can control or delete their data, and disclose the third-party SDKs and services your app uses. The finished document must meet the requirements of Google Play, the Apple App Store, and any data-protection laws that apply to your users.</p>

    <p>A privacy policy is not optional. Google Play, the Apple App Store, and privacy regulations around the world all require one before your app can be published or lawfully process personal data. Below is a practical, step-by-step guide to writing one that covers every platform and major regulation.</p>

    <nav class="toc">
